---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout>
  <main>
    <section class="hero container">
      <h1>A <span class="brand">control room</span> for your<br/>AI engineering team.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Start with one agent. Grow to a tribe.
        Chepherd watches your team's work,
        catches drift, and keeps the human in command.
        One install. Local-first. Open-source.
      </p>
      <a class="cta" href="/download">Get chepherd</a>
      <a class="cta secondary" href="/docs">Read the docs</a>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">How it works</h2>
        <div class="grid">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Meet Adam</h3>
            <p>Your default working agent. Talk to Adam like you'd talk to Claude — but Adam can recruit specialists when the work warrants it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Meet Chepherd</h3>
            <p>Adam's watcher. The prophet figure. Reads Adam's work from above and catches stuck patterns, quality drift, scope creep. 4-eyes principle, always on.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Grow the team</h3>
            <p>When Adam spawns a peer (or you do), it appears in the dashboard. Agents talk to each other via <code>@target</code>. You can join the conversation any time.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Three ways to use it</h2>
        <div class="grid">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Terminal (TUI)</h3>
            <p>Developers + SSH'd servers. <code>chepherd run</code> in any shell. k9s-style live dashboard.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Browser (web)</h3>
            <p>For non-developers. Open localhost:8080 after install. Full dashboard, xterm.js-rendered panes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Phone (iOS/Android)</h3>
            <p>Push notifications, quick replies, remote control. Pair to your laptop with a QR code or connect to a hosted Sovereign.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Quick start</h2>
        <pre class="code-block mono"><code># macOS / Linux / Windows — pick your OS
curl -fsSL https://chepherd.io/install.sh | sh

# Or Homebrew
brew install chepherd

# Run it
chepherd run</code></pre>
        <p style="color: #aaa; margin-top: 1rem;">
          Your provider (Claude / Anthropic API / OpenRouter / OpenOva NewAPI / Ollama) sets up in 60 seconds via <code>chepherd setup</code>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
